# Backup files and directories - CRITICAL SECURITY
backups/
*backup*/
*.sql
# A surgical un-ignore for the one numbered migration tracked in this
# repo (Task #794). The historical Drizzle-generated SQL files
# (0000–0009, plus the ad-hoc `fix_submission_vendors_schema.sql`) are
# intentionally NOT tracked: production has historically been kept in
# sync via `drizzle-kit push`, and re-introducing them as executable
# numbered files would make them "pending" on environments whose
# `schema_migrations` was baselined without them, where they would fail
# (they are not idempotent — raw `CREATE TYPE` / `CREATE TABLE`).
# The negation is placed AFTER the `*.sql` rule so gitignore precedence
# (last matching rule wins) keeps this single file trackable.
!migrations/0010_demands_residence_building_check.sql
